text: "River Deep - Mountain High" is a 1966 song by Ike & Tina Turner and is the title track to the 1966 studio album of the same name. It went to number 88 in the United States, number 3 in the United Kingdom, number 14 in Australia, number 12 in Ireland, number 1 in Spain and number 9 in the Netherlands. It has covered numerous times over the years including Four Tops featuring The Supremes in 1970 and when to number 14 in the United States and South Africa, number 12 in Ireland and number 11 in the United Kingdom. ==References== Category:1966 songs Category:Soul songs Category:Ike & Tina Turner songs Category:Deep Purple songs Category:Four Tops songs Category:The Supremes songs Category:Harry Nilsson songs Category:The Animals songs Category:Eric Burdon songs Category:Jimmy Barnes songs Category:Celine Dion songs Category:Bob Seger songs Category:Neil Diamond songs Category:Erasure songs Category:Beyoncé songs Category:Christina Aguilera songs Category:Darlene Love songs Category:Annie Lennox songs
